text:
Web scraping demo: Philadelphia Health Inspections
Let‚Äôs scrape data for restaurant inspections using the searchable database maintained by the Philadelphia Inquirer, available at: https://data.inquirer.com/inspections/


Getting the HTML content
We‚Äôll use the built-in ‚Äúrequests‚Äù module to request the content of the website and load it into Python.

import requests

Use a ‚Äúget‚Äù request to get the content:

url = "https://data.inquirer.com/inspections/"
r = requests.get(url)


type(r)

requests.models.Response



r.status_code

200




BeautifulSoup makes this much more manageable
BeautifulSoup makes it much easier to extract out different parts of a website.

from bs4 import BeautifulSoup

Initialize the ‚Äúsoup‚Äù object, using the content of our get request:

soup = BeautifulSoup(r.content, 'html.parser')



Making the HTML ‚Äúpretty‚Äù

print(soup.prettify())

