This is what you‚Äôll see if you use the Web Inspector


How to extract the content we want?
Two important functions

soup.select_one(selector): finds the first element matching the selector query and returns one element
soup.select(selector): finds all elements matching the selector

Recommended reading: Note on beautiful soup and css selectors in this week‚Äôs repository


To the Web Inspector!
We can use the web inspector to understand the structure of the website and identify the HTML tags that we want to extract content from.


Let‚Äôs select the first row
Web browsers will let us copy the CSS selector for individual elements.
Use: Right Click &gt; Copy &gt; Copy Selector

selector = "#inspection_unit_0"


# Select the first row
# NOTE: we are using "select_one()" to select only one matching element
first_row = soup.select_one(selector)


first_row

