But we need all of the rows!






Important



When you use Copy -&gt; Copy Selector, the copied css selector will only match the specific element you‚Äôve highlighted, no others!



Generalizing your selectors
We need to generalize the selector to just select all rows from the table, not just the first one. To do this, we‚Äôll need to go back to the web inspector and understand the structure of the website.






Tip



When trying to identify a general selector, try to look for common patterns, like shared class names or id strings, across the tags you want to extract.


In our case, it looks like the ‚ÄúinspectionUnit‚Äù class is shared across all of the row div elements


# Get all tags with the inspectionUnit class name
# Note we are using select() to select ALL elements
rows = soup.select('.inspectionUnit')


len(rows)

50



# get the first row
row = rows[0]

